title: For Sale:  Blackhawk Traverse/Pivot Bipod
postcontent: Almost brand-new Blackhawk Traverse/Pivot Bipod 6"-9" legs.  I purchased this from BassPro a couple weeks ago for $80 and just decided I didn't want them, will stick to using bags for a rest.  The legs work perfectly fine, I was impressed by their mechanical function.  This is the Traverse/Pivot model, so with the swing of one lever you can unlock so that you can traverse (left/right movement) your firearm while maintaining your bipod rest, or pivot (magazine changes, etc.).  Takes 15 seconds to put them on or off, they attach to sling mount on your firearm, and the mounting piece has two rubber pads that run the length so it won't nick or damage your stock.  Since it is out of the package, I will sell for $45.  The legs have literally been used at an indoor range once (never been outside), and taken off/on maybe 5 times.  Note: in the 2nd picture, there is a mount shown that I do not intend to sell.  The mount is a $20 piece from Caldwell that goes onto a Picatinny rail (AR-15 style) and gives you a sling swivel.  These bipod legs do not attach directly to a Picatinny rail (everyone I found that does was near or over $200).  I also purchased the mount from BassPro, but if it is make or break to also have this so you don't need to make your own trip, I will include it at-price ($20).  Reply to this email or text me at (913) 636-372 zero.  I will ship at-cost.  Thanks!
